<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-08-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-08-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="148" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d148">
                            <head><hi rend="italic"><gloss type="from">Consul-general at
                                        Shanghai</gloss> to <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-08-15"><hi rend="italic">August 15,
                                        1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Conger wires reaching Tsinan-fu to-day. Still imprisoned and
                                violently attacked by Chinese army. Dr. Inglis’s baby and 7 marines
                                dead. All other Americans alive. Considerable sickness. Allies
                                within 40 miles; gives us strong hope. Woodwards, Chicago, well.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Goodnow.</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>